# git learning notes 
(command line tool)
git is a free and open source distributed version control system designed to handle everything from small to very large projects with speed and efficiency.
it is also "time machine" for your code.
allows you to go back in time and see what your code looked like at a certain point in time. 

GitHub is a website and cloud-based service that helps developers store and manage their code, as well as track and control changes to their code.

"repo" is a storage space where your project lives.

commit - snapshot of your repository at a certain point in time

branch is a parallel version of a repository

git config --global user.name "aiddd1004"
git config --global user.email "ai_ibraim@kbtu.kz"

git config --global init.defaultBranch main
# default branch name 

git config --global core.autocrlf true
git config --global core.safecrlf warn
# line ending treatment for windows
 
mkdir work
cd work
touch hello.html
# creating hello world page

git init
# to create a Git repo from that directory.

git add hello.html
git commit -m "Initial Commit"
# adding the page to repository 

# repo status check
the repository stores the current state of the working directory, and there are no changes to record.

git log 
# view history of project


